<br>
<h2>User and event management</h2>
<div>
You can edit an event or user's details by clicking "Events" or "Users" in the admin dashboard, selecting the event or user to update info for, 
clicking the "edit" button, and then submitting the form to update their details.
<br>
Note that this allows you to grant admin access to other users.
</div>
<br>

<h2>Confirming user participation</h2>
<div>
For final confirmation that a member who signed up for an event is permitted to participate, you can navigate to the volunteer event in question under "Events"
click the "Confirm" or "Deny" button next to the name of the user you'd like to confirm.
<br>
This will also send the user an email. Until an admin does this, users will not be registered for the event!
</div>
<br>

<h2>Annoucement/Comment Management</h2>
<div>
The Announcements page can be found by clicking on the button in the bar at the top. As an administrator, you can post, edit, and delete annoucements or comments.
<br>
On the list of announcements, click "Post Announcement". This will open up a page that allows you to write a post in rich text, and attach images or link to other websites.
<br>
On the page of any given announcement, you can use the relevant buttons to edit or delete the announcement as a whole, or delete comments from other users.
</div>
<br>

<h2>Event Logs</h2>
<div>
For debugging purposes, an admin can see a list of all "Event Logs" from the admin dashboard. An Event Log is just a marker that a user has signed up for an event.
<br>
This page can be sorted to show things such as all events a user has signed up for, all users who have signed up for an event, or all confirmed users for an event.
</div>
<br>

<h2>User Log Data</h2>
<div>
From the admin dashboard, user participation data can be downloaded as a CSV file.
<br>
This file contains the name, email, and total volunteer hours of all registered users.
</div>
